cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a computer-aided diagnosis (CAD) tool based on deep learning techniques to classify proximal femur fractures on x-ray images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the integration of the proposed CAD tool into daily clinical routine, which suggests that it may belong to the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the interface between humans and AI-powered machines in supporting medical decisions, which suggests that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
